org.jdbi.v3.core

Class StatementContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jdbi.v3.core.StatementContext

  • public final class StatementContext
extends Object
    The statement context provides a means for passing client specific information through the evaluation of a statement. The context is not used by jDBI internally, but will be passed to all statement customizers. This makes it possible to parameterize the processing of the tweakable parts of the statement processing cycle.

      • isConcurrentUpdatable

        public boolean isConcurrentUpdatable()
        Return if the statement should be concurrent updatable. If this returns true, the concurrency level of the created ResultSet will be ResultSet.CONCUR_UPDATABLE, otherwise the result set is not updatable, and will have concurrency level ResultSet.CONCUR_READ_ONLY.
        Returns:
        if the statement generated should be concurrent updatable.
